would happen if the 50+ fire pets got access to some of the spells corresponding to its actual level. There will most likely be some tweeking of the spell list compared to how it is on test if it ever goes live. There is also the thing with the pets mana pool, which is small.<br>
<br>
The lv 52 and lv 58 fire pets as they are has a very situational use and basically involves resummoning the pet untill you get one that cast stun (the pets come in 'flavours', some liking to root, some to nuke and some to stun). The nukes it casts are all less than lv 30 nukes. The lv 63 fire pet has the same spell list as the other pets and against the mobs you fight at lv 63 is one of the biggest jokes in the game.<br>
<br>
A change to the pet has therefore been needed for a very long time.<br>
<br>
Ii would be cool if I got a pet that cast ice comet, but I can live without it. I just want a pet that I know I can summon, which isn't a joke.<br>
<br>
The AI that conteols NPC's and pets got changed a while back and they did get a little smarter in their choice and use of nukes. However, the pets as they are, are already difficult to control at times and I can see some major headackes trying to control a pet that is much more a caster than the other pets.<br>
